      "source": [
        "An ordinary analysis performed only on day twenty rejects\n",
        "`{python} f\"{fpr_planned_analysis:.1%}\"` of the time, close to the intended 5%.\n",
        "Checking the ordinary p-value daily and stopping at the first rejection raises\n",
        "the rate to `{python} f\"{fpr_daily_ordinary:.0%}\"`. This is below the 64%\n",
        "independence benchmark because the twenty analyses reuse the same accumulating\n",
        "data. It is nevertheless several times the specified 5%. SAVI rejects\n",
        "`{python} f\"{fpr_daily_savi:.1%}\"` of the same null experiments. This rate\n",
        "need not equal 5%: under the method's assumptions, the probability of a false\n",
        "rejection at any time is asymptotically at most 5%, so the probability of\n",
        "rejecting by day twenty is also at most 5% and can be lower.\n",
        "\n",
        "Daily stopping also inflates the absolute effect reported at rejection.\n",
