        "## Scenario 5: decide whether to roll back a canary\n",
        "\n",
        "A canary sends a small share of traffic to a new service version before a\n",
        "full rollout. If the version reduces conversion, hourly monitoring can limit\n",
        "the number of users exposed before rollback. An ordinary confidence interval\n",
        "provides pointwise coverage for the prespecified two-day analysis. A rule that\n",
        "rolls back at the first hourly threshold crossing makes the analysis time\n",
        "data-dependent, whereas a confidence sequence provides simultaneous coverage\n",
        "across the hourly reviews.\n",
        "\n",
        "The team will tolerate a conversion loss of no more than 1 pp, so -1 pp is the\n",
        "decision boundary. With 500 new users per arm each hour:\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Roll back** if the upper endpoint is below -1 pp; every effect compatible\n",
        "  with the data implies a loss greater than 1 pp.\n",
        "- **Promote** if the lower endpoint is above -1 pp; a loss of 1 pp or more has\n",
        "  been ruled out.\n",
        "- **Continue** while the sequence contains -1 pp.\n",
