        "`{python} f\"{stopped_share['adjusted'][-1]:.0%}\"` of experiments, compared with\n",
        "`{python} f\"{stopped_share['unadjusted'][-1]:.0%}\"` without the pre-experiment\n",
        "metric.\n",
        "\n",
        "At day twenty, the Monte Carlo mean treatment estimates are\n",
        "`{python} f\"{mean_estimate['unadjusted']:.3f}\"` without adjustment and\n",
        "`{python} f\"{mean_estimate['adjusted']:.3f}\"` with adjustment, against a true\n",
        "average effect of `{python} f\"{ADJUSTMENT_EFFECT:.3f}\"`. Both are close to the\n",
        "true value in these 200 simulations; the adjusted analysis is more precise\n",
        "because the covariate predicts the outcome.\n",
        "\n",
        "To check whether adjustment inflates false positives in this design, we repeat\n",
        "the simulation with an average treatment effect of zero. Across\n",
        "`{python} ADJUSTMENT_NULL_SIMULATIONS` experiments, the SAVI p-value fell below\n",
        "0.05 by day twenty in `{python} int(adjustment_null_rejections)` runs\n",
        "(`{python} f\"{adjustment_null_rejection_rate:.1%}\"`). This check would reveal a\n",
        "large size distortion, but 200 runs cannot estimate a 5% rate precisely.\n",
        "\n",
        "Regression adjustment should use only variables measured before treatment.\n",
        "Conditioning on a post-treatment variable can bias the treatment coefficient.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Apply SAVI in PyFixest\n",
        "\n",
        "SAVI uses the same regression refit at each review regardless of the decision\n",
        "rule. Before monitoring, choose the outcome, regression specification,\n",
        "covariance estimator, and tested coefficient, and keep them fixed. Append the\n",
        "newly completed experimental units at each review and refit that specification.\n",
        "Here, `treated` is the randomized treatment indicator and `converted` is the\n",
        "primary metric."
